HEADWORD: Housewive
<hw>House"wive`</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To manage with skill and
economy, as a housewife or other female manager; to economize.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Conferred those moneys on the nuns, which since they have well
<qex>housewived</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Housewifely</ent>⟦br⟧
